meanings.definition: To fly faster or farther than
meanings.sent1: The bird outflew its companions to reach the destination first.
meanings.sent2: The cheetah outflew the other animals in the race.
meanings.sent3: The superhero outflew the speeding bullet with ease.
meanings.sent4: Her dreams outflew the limitations of reality.
meanings.sent5: The kite outflew the wind, dancing gracefully in the sky.

meanings.sent1: The eagle outflew all other birds in the sky.
meanings.sent2: The jet plane outflew the propeller aircraft.
meanings.sent3: The tiny hummingbird outflew the big hawk, surprising everyone.
meanings.sent4: His determination outflew his fear of heights.
meanings.sent5: The champion racehorse outflew its competitors, winning the race.

meanings.sent1: The butterfly outflew from the garden into the meadow.
meanings.sent2: The bat outflew the cave to explore the night sky.
meanings.sent3: The mischievous fairy outflew from her hiding spot, giggling.
meanings.sent4: His thoughts outflew from the classroom to the playground.
meanings.sent5: The paper airplane outflew the window, soaring into the unknown.
